There’s been tears, I’ve been incredibly stressed and even wondered if could carry on. But I have, I have found the strength for so many things I’d never thought I’d be able to do. I’m proud of myself.

But best of all, I’ve learnt to like myself. I’ve been able to find myself. I’ve had the best support from my closest friends and family(and Benji) and I wouldn’t change the past year. It’s taught me a lot and made me realise a lot of important lessons.

the last year hasn’t been great for obvious reasons, but for me personally it’s been one of the best. I’ve left a relationship I was unhappy in, lived independently whilst undertaking the hardest year as a student nurse, whilst on placement through a pandemic.
